dc_title_s: Poland 1:100,000. Dzialdowo, sheet M-14. A.M.S. M651 (G.S.G.S. 4416)
dc_description_s: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4416. Alternate title: Dzialdowo, Poland. Polyconic projection. Russian belt 4 grid. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With a glossary. Compiled from Poland, 1:100,000, German General Staff, sheet 43, 1933; Poland, 1:100,000, Military Geographic Institute, sheets 36-29, 1942; 36-30, 1930; 37-29, 1942 and 37-30, 1935. Road classification in Poland based on British intelligence reports, 1943.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
